Nuchal cysts syndromes: etiology, pathogenesis, and prenatal diagnosis. We examined 10 fetuses with nuchal cysts and compared the findings with 32 cases from the literature. Based on their characteristics, we propose that nuchal cysts are signs of four causally and pathogenetically different entities: cystic nuchal blebs present in otherwise normal fetuses as a postmortem change 45,X fetuses who have a particular appearance and multiple congenital malformations